## 2.4 Query Embedding Flow (CRITICAL)

At search time, we need to embed the **query** (not just documents):

```
Query: "machine learning optimization"
    │
    ├──→ [Model2Vec query embed] ──→ ~1ms (in-process, blocking)
    │         256-dim vector           │
    │                                  │
    │                         cosine vs fast_embeddings
    │                                  │
    │                                  ▼
    │                          Fast results
    │
    └──→ [MiniLM query embed via daemon] ──→ ~10ms (async)
              384-dim vector                    │
                                               │
                                      cosine vs quality_embeddings
                                               │
                                               ▼
                                        Refined results
```

### Key Point: Index vs Query Embeddings
- **Index time**: Pre-compute document embeddings for BOTH models
- **Search time**: Embed query with BOTH models (fast in-process, quality via daemon)

```rust
impl TwoTierSearcher {
    pub async fn search(&self, query: &str, limit: usize) -> impl Stream<Item = SearchPhase> {
        // Phase 1: Fast query embedding (blocking, in-process)
        let fast_query = self.fast.embed(query)?;  // ~1ms
        let fast_scores = cosine_similarity(&fast_query, &self.index.fast_embeddings);
        let fast_results = self.top_k(&fast_scores, limit);

        yield SearchPhase::Initial { results: fast_results, latency_ms: ... };

        // Phase 2: Quality query embedding (async, via daemon)
        match self.quality.embed(&[query], Some(&self.config.quality_model), None).await {
            Ok(quality_query) => {
                let quality_scores = cosine_similarity(&quality_query[0], &self.index.quality_embeddings);
                let (fast_norm, quality_norm) = normalize_scores(&fast_scores, &quality_scores);
                let blended = blend_scores(&fast_norm, &quality_norm, self.config.blend_factor);
                let refined_results = self.top_k(&blended, limit);

                yield SearchPhase::Refined { results: refined_results, ... };
            }
            Err(e) if self.config.fallback_on_daemon_error => {
                yield SearchPhase::RefinementFailed { error: e.to_string() };
            }
            Err(e) => return Err(e),
        }
    }
}
```

